# Published JSON Schemas are served at stable, version-segmented URLs
# (/schemas/<name>/v1.json) that editors and CI pin against. Within a major
# version the file is updated in place when the generating Rust types change,
# so it must NOT be cached long or immutably — clients would strand on a stale
# schema. Short TTL plus revalidation lets a regenerated v1 propagate while
# still allowing CDN/edge caching.
/schemas/*
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=300, must-revalidate
